# SkyWeb Change Log

Detailed implementation notes for SkyWeb Analytics. The README now stays focused on current status, commands, and roadmap.

## DN-6 — SkyWeb Profile and Preferences in C#

- Added native ASP.NET Core/C# endpoints for `GET/PATCH /api/skyweb/profile`.
- Added native ASP.NET Core/C# endpoints for `GET/PATCH /api/skyweb/preferences`.
- Added native ASP.NET Core/C# endpoints for `GET/PATCH /api/skyweb/alert-preferences`.
- Added native SkyWeb permission enforcement for profile, dashboard preferences, and alert preferences.
- Added C# profile service preserving `skyweb.user_profiles` and `skyweb.vw_user_profiles` contracts.
- Added C# preference service preserving `skyweb.user_preferences` and `skyweb.vw_user_preferences` contracts.
- Preserved default insertion, JSONB storage, validation, and existing React response shapes.
- Kept saved views, dashboards, alert rules, alert notifications, and Signal Center on the temporary SkyServer proxy for DN-7/DN-8.

## DN-5.2 — Indicator Series Regclass/NaN Fix

- Cast PostgreSQL `to_regclass(...)` checks to `text` before Dapper/Npgsql materialization.
- Scrubbed PostgreSQL numeric `NaN` values into JSON-safe `null` values for indicator series responses.
- Stabilized native C# indicator-series reads used by dashboard mini charts.

## DN-5 — Authentication in C#

- Added native `/api/auth/login`, `/api/auth/logout`, `/api/auth/change-password`, `/api/auth/me`, and `/api/auth/permissions`.
- Preserved opaque bearer-token sessions using SHA-256 session-token hashes in `auth.sessions`.
- Preserved permission reads from `auth.vw_user_permissions` and login/audit event writes.

## DN-4 — Public Macro REST Endpoints in C#

- Replaced `/api/public/macro/*` proxy fallback with native ASP.NET Core/C# endpoints.
- Kept auth and SkyWeb user features on proxy fallback during the migration.

## DN-0 to DN-3 — .NET Transition Foundation

- Added `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Api` and `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Client`.
- Added health, DB health, Swagger, CORS, and local dev scripts.
- Wired the copied React client to `SkyWeb.Api` with a temporary proxy bridge to SkyServer.
